g.text: 1st Battalion sailed from Messina for independent landing by 231st Brigade near Pizzo, Italy in rear of enemy forces opposing main landing of 8th Army at Reggio.
1st Battalion in assault landing at Porto S Venere by 231st Brigade. Strong enemy counter attacks driven off.
1st Battalion with 231st Brigade led 8th Army advance to the River Amoto.

128th Brigade (2nd, 1/4th and 5th Battalions) assault Battalions of 46th Division in the invasion landings by 5th Army at Salerno. 2/4th Battalion (Bn HQ, C and D companies) landed as part of 21 Beach Group at Salerno and fought in the bridgehead under 167th, 133rd and 23rd Armoured Brigades.
128th Brigade (2nd, 1/4th and 5th Battalions) in fierce fighting for White Cross Hill and Cava (Salerno).
1st Battalion left Italy for UK via Sicily with 231 Brigade.
128th Brigade (2nd, 1/4th and 5th Battalions) in assault crossing of River Volturno.
1st Battalion and 231st Brigade sailed from Syracuse in the ‘Durban’ for UK as part of 50th Division.
Attempted crossing of River Garigliano by 128th Bde (2nd, 1/4th & 5th Bns).
5th Bn (128th Bde) advanced by night and occupied Monte Ornito and Hill 771 (2,500ft above Garigliano Valley) and held them against counter-attacks whilst under continuous shell and mortar fire.
5th Bn (128th Bde) advanced from Ornito and captured Monte Cerosola and, assisted by Z Coy 2nd Bn, held this ridge also for 48hrs until relieved by 1st Guards Bde. 200 casualties in 5 days’ fighting.
2/4th Bn re-formed in Nov 43 from 20 & 21 Beach Groups, joined 28th Bde, 4th Div and took over Rocca D’Evandro Sector on River Garigliano.
128th Bde (2nd, 1/4th & 5th Bns) relieved by 12th Bde, 4th Div in Suja area in preparation for reorganisation and rest with 46th Div in Middle East after 6 months continuous operations.
128th Bde sailed from Traranto for Alexandria and subsequently moved to Quassasin, Nathaniya (Palestine) and Baalbee (Syria).
2/4th Bn (4th Div) in Saint Elia – Belvedere are NE of Cassino, until relieved by NZ Div on 18 Apr.
4th Div night assault on Gustav Line. 2/4th Bn ferried the other two Bns of 28 Bde across River Gari, South of Cassino, under heavy fire.
2/4th Bn carried out successful flank attack with tanks against strong enemy positions holding up 4 Div attack and cleared the whole of 28 Bde objective, taking 200 prisoners.
2/4th Bn attacked across River Pioppetto under heavy fire and captured Vertechi. Capt R Wakeford awarded VC. The Bn had 198 casualties between 11 and 14 May.
2/4th advanced with 28 Bde (4 Div) south of Lake Trasimene and captured Vaiano, La Villa and Lopi from troops of 1st German Parachute Division.
4 Div attack on Monte Scalari (Chianti Mountains). 2/4th Bn (28 Bde) captured Santa Lucia and Point 531 in conjunction with 12 Bde attack on left.
2/4th Battalion held Ceremonial Parade for HM King George VI at Sansavino (Nr Arezzo). Captain Wakeford decorated with VC.
128 Brigade (2nd, 1/4th and 5th Battalions) after four months refitting and training in Palestine and Syria, returned to Italy and concentrated in the Bastardo area.
2/4th Battalion at the capture of Belvedere.
2/4th Battalion at capture of La Croce and Vicchio.
2/4th Battalion carry out a 15 mile opposed advance to River Arno.
2/4th Battalion move to Assisi for rest and reorganisation.
128th Brigade (2nd, 1/4th and 5th Battalions) leading Brigade of 46 Division; assaulted the Gothic Line, penetrated 12 miles and captured M Grosso and M Bartolo.
Capture of M Gridolfo, a strong point of the Gothic Line, by 1/4th and 2nd Battalions. Lt GR Norton MM (attached 1/4th Battalion) awarded the VC.
2/4th Battalion in successful attack on Casa Bagli.
Gothic Line: Capture of Montescudo by 5th Battalion, after four hours close quarter fighting.
2/4th Battalion in night attack on Cerasola Ridge.
Gothic Line: 2nd and 1/4th Battalions in the crossing of River Fiumicino and the Battle for Montigallo.

Four Battalions of the Regiment in line in the attack on Forli, 2nd, 1/4th and 5th Battalions (128th Brigade, 46th Division) and 2/4th, left Battalion of 4th Division. They were all next to each other.
2/4th Battalion in night attack over River Cosina by 28th Brigade (4th Division) captured all objectives in face of stiff opposition.
128th Brigade (2nd, 1/4th and 5th Battalions) in advance from Cosina River to Lamone River.
Assault crossing of River Lamone and attack on Pideura Ridge by 128th Brigade (2nd, 1/4th and 5th Battalions).
128th Brigade (2nd, 1/4th and 5th Battalions) withdrawn to concentration area, south of Ancona, under orders for Greece.
